To create a responsive and visually appealing birthday web application using HTML, we'll need to use CSS for styling and JavaScript for dynamic functionality. Here's a basic structure:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Birthday App</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="style.css">
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Happy Birthday</h1>
    </header>
    <main>
        <section class="birthday-form">
            <form>
                <label for="name">Name:</label>
                <input type="text" id="name" name="name"><br><br>
                <label for="age">Age:</label>
                <input type="number" id="age" name="age"><br><br>
                <input type="submit" value="Submit">
            </form>
        </section>
        <section class="birthday-wish">
            <h2 id="wish"></h2>
        </section>
    </main>
    <script src="script.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
```

